Grifols SA (GRF)  aims to increase its sales
by 7 percent in 2012 and boost earnings before interest, tax,
depreciation and amortization to more than 700 million euros
($937 million),  Expansion  said, citing Chairman Victor Grifols.  The company, which already gets about 65 percent of revenue
from the U.S. and  Canada , will cut its debt by 400 million euros
in 2012 and will focus on generating cash, the newspaper cited
